<paragraph blockId="73.[189,1399,1220,1363]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
FRUIT. Ovoid to globose, accrescent at the apex, red when mature. Epicarp puberulent, with red to yellow simple hairs with granular ornamentation, ridged when dry, revealing the underlying reticulum of endocarp ridges. Mesocarp ca 
<quantity box="[588,682,1298,1324]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="100.0">100 µm</quantity>
thick when dry. Calyx persistent. Length 
<quantity box="[1187,1318,1297,1324]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="34.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="34.0">34–35 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[189,319,1336,1363]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="12.0">12–20 mm</quantity>
, thickness 
<quantity box="[446,547,1336,1363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
